────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Third-party asset provenance
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The MIT LICENSE covers Bureau's source code (bash scripts, SKILL.md,
documentation prose, CSS, HTML rendering). It does NOT automatically
extend to every asset in this repo. Third-party assets:

1. Hero image — `docs/assets/hero.png`
   AI-generated via the codex CLI (gpt-image), rendered from a prompt
   authored for this project. Not derived from any pre-existing
   copyrighted work. Distributed under the same MIT terms.

2. Design system tokens — `docs/site/assets/colors_and_type.css`
   Color / spacing / motion values are carried over verbatim from
   Kai's private Brainhuggers codebase (production tokens.css). The
   values themselves are functional facts (RGB triples, pixel counts,
   easing curves) and are contributed to Bureau under the MIT
   license. The overall visual "look" — hot pink on near-black — is
   the same design language used by the Brainhuggers brand, but no
   proprietary Brainhuggers materials (logos, wordmarks, imagery)
   ship in this repo.

3. Type stack — system-sans only
   The `--font-display` and `--font-body` CSS variables name
   'Babcock' and 'Silka' as the first font-family for backwards
   compatibility with private-copy consumers holding a valid Atipo
   Foundry license. Bureau ships NO font files; system-sans is the
   fallback and the only stack most viewers will see.

4. Speckit integration
   Bureau's `/bureau-init` skill delegates to `spec-kit`
   (github.com/github/spec-kit) via `specify init`. Speckit is
   pinned to a specific version (see `BUREAU_SPECKIT_VERSION` in
   SKILL.md) and installed by the operator; Bureau does not
   redistribute speckit code.

5. Third-party skills referenced in docs (caveman, Headroom, etc.)
   are external projects with their own licenses. Bureau's
   docs/token-efficiency.md links to them but redistributes no
   code from them.

